  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3e1cd92da80c7495a8fe7eb91fa80c2f, type: 3}
  m_Name: Poppy
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Plants.PlantData
  displayName: Poppy
  audioClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 2181df6a44bfcdc4a804cf16a104660d, type: 3}
  environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  environmentLayers: []
  environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  poem:
    text: "The Poppy\n\nSummer set lip to earth's bosom bare, \nAnd left the flush'd
      print in a poppy there; \nLike a yawn of fire from the grass it came, \nAnd
      the fanning wind puff'd it to flapping flame. \nWith burnt mouth red like a
      lion's it drank \nThe blood of the sun as he slaughter'd sank, \nAnd dipp'd
      its cup in the purpurate shine \nWhen the eastern conduits ran with wine. \nTill
      it grew lethargied with fierce bliss \n,And hot as a swinked gipsy is, \nAnd
      drowsed in sleepy savageries, \nWith mouth wide a-pout for a sultry kiss.\n\nFrancis
      Thompson"
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  contextInfos:
  - text: Poppies grow in the midst of the summer, red, hot, and they often don't
      keep.
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: It's german name is Klatschmohn, literally "clapping poppy". This Comes
      from an old game About love.
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: You fold a petal into a little pouch, bring your hands together with a
      smack, and the louder it bursts, the more your love is said to love you back.
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: "In China, the common Poppy is known as y\xFAm\u011Bir\xE9n, \"Yu the Beauty\"."
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: Consort Yu took her own life as her Lovers army fell. Where she was burried,
      red poppies grew. Perishing for love.
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
  - text: "Song of Consort Yu:\n\n\u6F22\u5175\u5DF2\u7565\u5730\uFF0C\n\u56DB\u9762\u695A\u6B4C\u8072\u3002\n\u5927\u738B\u7FA9\u6C23\u76E1\uFF0C\n\u8CE4\u59BE\u4F55\u804A\u751F\u3002\n\nHan
      forces have conquered our land;\nSurrounded by Chu songs;\nMy King's spirits
      are low;\nWhy then should I live?"
    contextImage: {fileID: 0}
    imageWidth: 0.5
    imageFeather: -1
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
    environmentLayers: []
    environmentVerticalOffset: 0
